<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF9BFFE7FE0A1E38878BB65B" bold="true" box="[403,735,1077,1104]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="811">Diaphanocypris meridana</emphasis>
(Furtos, 1936)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF9BFFE7FF591E66866EB6E7" blockId="12.[160,1155,1131,1260]" pageId="12" pageNumber="811">
We found this elongated ostracod in artificial impoundments. Our records include the water hazards at the Herman E. Moore Golf Course, on the University of the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF9BFFE7FC771E8081D7B6AD" box="[1006,1155,1165,1190]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="12" pageNumber="811">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
St. Thomas campus, and the upper impoundment on Mahogany Run ghut. We also found it in ornamental aquatic garden plantings in Tillet Gardens.
</paragraph>
